[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 4 673 195, with reports of cases by 217 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 98.2% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA, with more than 1.49 million confirmed cases, now represents 31.9% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 310 082 deaths have been reported, with 305 449 (98.5%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Spain is number 2, and Russia is number 3, followed by the UK, Italy, Brazil, France, Germany, Turkey, and Iran as number 10. China is now number 13. Russia reported the highest number of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (9200) followed by USA (6169) , Brazil (4654), UK (3450), Saudi Arabia (2840), India (2722), and Mexico (2437) reporting the 7th-highest 24-hour newly confirmed case numbers. - Mod.UBA]

