[3] USA: Kansas prison outbreak
Date: Fri 15 May 2020
Source: KOAM-TV [edited]
https://www.koamnewsnow.com/the-largest-prison-in-kansas-reports-750-positive-tests-for-covid-19/


The Lansing Correctional Facility in Kansas sees 750 inmates test positive for COVID-19, with an Iola family saying their family member is one of them.

30-year-old [PK] doesn't have severe symptoms, but he is being housed with inmates who do. He also hasn't seen a doctor since being diagnosed.

His mother says it's scary since there's so much that they don't know about the virus or what's happening.

[Byline: Augustus Brunetti]

